<!-- How It Works -->
<section class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header centered">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">The Technology</span>
            <h2>How Drip Irrigation Works</h2>
            <p>Instead of spraying water over the top of a field, drip irrigation runs supply lines along the soil surface or underground — putting water exactly where plants can use it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="three-col-grid" style="margin-top:40px;">
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🚰</div>
                <h3>1. Supply & Filtration</h3>
                <p>Water enters through a mainline, passes through filters and pressure regulators to protect emitters, and is conditioned for your water quality and field pressure.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">〰️</div>
                <h3>2. Distribution Lines</h3>
                <p>Driplines or drip tape run along each row or plant zone. Sub-surface placement eliminates evaporation and keeps foliage dry — reducing disease pressure.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">💧</div>
                <h3>3. Root-Zone Emission</h3>
                <p>Precision emitters release controlled, low-volume water directly into the root zone on whatever schedule your crops and soil demand — managed automatically or manually.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

