<section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:760px;">
        <div class="section-header centered">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">Common Questions</span>
            <h2>Drip Irrigation FAQ</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-list">
            <details class="faq-item"><summary>What's the difference between drip tape and dripline?</summary><p>Drip tape is thin-walled and typically used for one to three seasons in annual crops. Driplines are thick-walled, pressure-compensating systems designed for permanent crops and can last 15–20 years underground.</p></details>
            <details class="faq-item"><summary>How do I choose emitter flow rate and spacing?</summary><p>Your certified dealer will size emitters based on your crop type, soil texture, row spacing, and water supply. Getting this right is critical — it's one of the most important parts of a system design.</p></details>
            <details class="faq-item"><summary>Can drip irrigation handle slopes and uneven terrain?</summary><p>Yes. Pressure-compensating (PC) emitters maintain uniform flow regardless of elevation changes, making them ideal for hillside orchards and irregular fields.</p></details>
            <details class="faq-item"><summary>How do I prevent clogging?</summary><p>Proper filtration at the head of the system is essential. DripSmart filter products are matched to your water quality and emitter type to prevent clogging over the system's entire life.</p></details>
            <details class="faq-item"><summary>Where do I buy DripSmart drip systems?</summary><p>DripSmart products are sold and installed through our network of certified dealers. Find your nearest dealer to get a system designed and quoted for your specific operation.</p></details>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center mt-lg">
            <a href="/find-a-dealer" class="btn-primary">Find Your Local Dealer</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
